# Announcements

Announcements are short messages displayed on [delivery sheet PDFs](/deliveries) at specific depots. They are a quick way to communicate important information to the people handling the delivery at a particular location, for example a reminder to bring back reusable bags or a notice about an exceptional schedule change.

You can manage announcements from [Other > Announcements](/announcements).

## How It Works {#how-it-works}

Each announcement is a short translated text (up to 140 characters) that you target to one or more **depots** and one or more **deliveries**. The text is then printed in bold at the top of the corresponding depot's delivery sheet.

Only one announcement can exist per depot and delivery combination. If you need different messages for different depots on the same delivery, simply create separate announcements.

> Announcements are not visible to members in their online account; they only appear on the printed delivery sheets.

## Creating an Announcement {#creating}

From the [announcements page](/announcements), click "New announcement" and fill in:

- **Text**: The message to display, in each of your organization's languages. Keep it short and actionable (140 characters max).
- **Depots**: Select one or more depots where the announcement should appear.
- **Deliveries**: Select one or more upcoming deliveries for the announcement.

The announcement will appear on the delivery sheet PDF for each selected depot on each selected delivery.

## Active and Past {#active-past}

Announcements are automatically categorized:

- **Active**: Linked to at least one upcoming delivery. These are the announcements currently in effect.
- **Past**: All linked deliveries have already occurred. Past announcements are kept for reference but have no further effect.

No manual archiving is needed, announcements move to "Past" on their own once all their deliveries have passed.

## Practical Examples {#examples}

Here are a few common uses for announcements:

- "Please bring back your <%= Basket.model_name.human(count: 2).downcase %>!"
- "Exceptional closing on Dec 26, no delivery"
- "New pickup hours: 4–7 PM starting next week"

## Permissions {#permissions}

Creating and editing announcements requires **write** access to the "Announcements" feature in your [permission settings](/permissions). See the [permissions handbook page](/handbook/permissions) for details.
